<div id="definitions">
<h3 data-target="definitionslist">Definitions <span class="rotate">&gt;</span></h3> 
<div id="definitionslist">
<p id="climate_policy_content">
<b>Climate policy:</b> Legislative actions, executive actions, announced plans, recommended goals, and other programs.
</p>
<p id="energy_supply_content">
<b>Energy Supply: </b>Renewable Portfolio Standards (RPS); 100% Clean and Renewable Energy Targets; other major state policies, plans, and programs relating to energy supply.
</p>
<p id="transportation_content">
<b>Transportation:</b> ZEV mandates; low carbon fuel standards; MOUs; other major state collaborations, initiatives, policies, plans, and programs relating to transportation.
</p>
<p id="industry_content">
<b>Industry: </b>Status of carbon pricing; appliance standards and extent of federal preemption; other major state initiatives relating to industry.
</p>
<p id="buildings_content">
<b>Buildings: </b>Major energy efficiency codes and policies; green building incentives; combined heat and power (CHP); adoption of International Energy Conservation Code (IECC) or American Society of Heating, Refrigerating, and Air-Conditioning Engineers (ASHRAE) Standards; other major state initiatives relating to buildings and energy efficiency.
</p>
<p id="LAF_content">
<b>Natural &amp; Working Lands, Agriculture, and Forestry: </b>Major initiatives, policies, plans, and programs for land use planning; agriculture; forestry.
</p>
<p id="cross_sector_content">
<b>Cross-sector: </b>GHG emission reduction targets; policies which apply across sectors; and general climate policies such as Californias economy-wide cap-and-trade program.
</p>
</div>
